                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; names of the donors; name of the king;
                           a few lines on the incipit page of the Text, alternating with black
                           lines; incipit of each section of the text; names of Hebrew letters in
                           Ps. 118; abbreviations; some other words: e.g., halle luya (e.g., fols.
                           9rb, 24vb), ṣällǝyu (e.g., fol. 14rb), wa-kāʿǝba (e.g., fols. 14vb,
                           15rb), wa-yǝbälu (e.g., fols. 19rb, 19vb), ʾǝgäle (e.g., fols. 25rb,
                           96ra), qǝdmä wangel (e.g., fols. 30ra, 53va); elements of Ethiopic
                           numerals; elements of the punctuation signs and text dividers.</seg>
                     </handNote>
