                              ኃይለ፡ ማርያም፡ ወለተ፡ ሥላሴ፡ ወለተ፡ ማርያም፡ ወለተ፡ ትንሣኤ። ዘአጽሐፈቶ፡ በንዋያ፡ ወወሀበቶ፡ ለታቦተ፡
                              ማርያም፡ ታብር፡ እንተ፡ ትሰመይ፡ ማይ፡ ራዛ። …</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> The note states that Walatta Mikāʾel donated the book to the
                              church of Māryām Tabǝr (?) which is called May Raza. It also mentions
                              her parents Walda Māryām and Lahǝyä Dǝngǝl, her husband gǝra ʾazmač
                              Habta Śǝllāse and her children. The head of the monastery Ḫāyla
                              ʾIyasus is mentioned as the scribe. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- <locus target="#2r">2r</locus>: Crude drawing of a cross
                           (?).&#xD; - The title of the book is crudely written on <locus target="#2r">2r</locus>.&#xD; - The names of the donors are written on
                              <locus target="#130vb">130vb</locus>.&#xD; - A crude frame in red ink
                           is drawn around four lines: <locus target="#59va">59va</locus>.&#xD; -
                           Corrections written over erasures: e.g., <locus target="#15ab">15ab</locus>, 44rb, 52ra, 53vb, 54ra.&#xD; - Omitted letters or words
                           inserted interlineally: e.g., <locus target="#3rb">3rb</locus>, 4rb, 5ra,
                           6vb, 7vab.&#xD; - Tamallas-sign indicating the place where the omission,
                           written in the outer or upper margin, belongs: e.g., <locus target="#9va">9va</locus>, 13ra, 15va, 27ra, 29rb.&#xD; - Compressed script: e.g.,
                              <locus from="28vb" to="30ra">28vb-30ra</locus>, 47va-48va,
                           52vb-53va.&#xD; - አም ቷቲ ሙአ አን ፋሲ (musical annotation signs?) is written
                           in very small letters above the abbreviation ሃ፡ ሃ፡ ሃ፡ ሃ፡: e.g., <locus target="#9va">9va</locus>b, 10rab, 10vab, 12rab.</item>
